parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to unexpected stops, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded, which can be a safety risk, especially when driving with children or in extreme weather conditions.
symptoms: The fuel gauge shows an incorrect reading
indicating more fuel in the tank than is actually present
or suddenly drops to empty despite having recently filled up; the vehicle may stall or shut down due to lack of fuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning sliding doors can cause inconvenience, safety risks, and potential damage to the vehicle. Water build-up in the door track can lead to rust and corrosion, while stuck doors can obstruct entry and exit.
symptoms: Sliding doors get stuck randomly
require excessive force to open
and may have unknown burn marks on the floorboard. Water build-up is present in the door track.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rattling noise from the windows can be a distraction while driving, causing discomfort and annoyance to the occupants.
symptoms: Rattling noise is present in one or both passenger-side windows
which can worsen over time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The repeated failure of the power window motor can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver and passengers, and may lead to safety issues if the window becomes stuck in a position that obstructs the driver's view.
symptoms: The power window motor stops working
the window does not roll up or down
the window gets stuck in a position.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the vehicle and loss of power can cause accidents, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds, and can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the engine light comes on
the vehicle struggles to move
the vehicle drives very slowly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding doors can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver and passengers, and may lead to safety issues if the doors do not close properly.
symptoms: The sliding doors do not close automatically
the doors do not close properly
the doors get stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can lead to inconvenience and discomfort to the driver and passengers, and may cause safety issues if the vehicle is stuck in a dangerous location.
symptoms: The vehicle does not start
the battery dies
the vehicle needs to be towed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause loss of control, accidents, and even death, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Slow steering response in cold weather
noise from the steering system
metal shavings in the power steering reservoir
dragging or popping noise from the steering
and sudden loss of steering control.
